- [Man #2] Go ahead, shoot the dice, man.

24:13.490 --> 24:17.030
Shoot the dice. Shoot the dice.
Shoot the dice.

24:18.330 --> 24:21.830
That's right. That's right, man.
That's right.

25:21.850 --> 25:24.520
[Inaudible Dialogue]

25:44.290 --> 25:46.960
(Phone Ringing)

27:41.570 --> 27:45.410
(Doorbell Rings)

28:10.980 --> 28:12.430
Noodles.

28:12.850 --> 28:16.060
I brought back the key to your clock.

28:24.990 --> 28:27.120
Lock the door.

28:30.120 --> 28:32.790
(Lock Clicks)

28:40.760 --> 28:43.090
When did you get back?

28:44.630 --> 28:48.140
- Today.
- Why?

28:49.470 --> 28:53.980
- They got in touch with me.
- Who?

28:54.140 --> 28:56.270
I thought you might know.

28:56.440 --> 28:58.020
Me?

28:58.190 --> 29:01.780
I don't know nothing
about nobody no more.

29:23.510 --> 29:25.970
You going to offer me a drink?

29:26.680 --> 29:29.470
Yeah, forgive me. Sure. Of course.

29:29.640 --> 29:31.680
Please sit down.

29:58.370 --> 30:00.290
Who's Robert Williams?

30:02.550 --> 30:03.880
I am.

30:10.390 --> 30:15.390
"We wish to inform you that following
the sale of the Beth Israel Cemetery...."

30:15.850 --> 30:20.060
Yeah, the synagogue sent these
out if you wanted to relocate
your loved ones.

30:20.230 --> 30:23.270
I got the same letter
on account of my father.

30:24.110 --> 30:28.570
Only the synagogue didn't send that.
I got that last week.

30:28.740 --> 30:31.530
The rabbi told me he sent those out
about eight months ago.

30:31.700 --> 30:35.080
Yeah, that's right.
That's just about when I got mine.

30:38.580 --> 30:40.620
So, what else did he say, the rabbi?

30:40.790 --> 30:44.420
He said that I was lucky.
The bodies of Philip Stein...

30:44.590 --> 30:49.380
...Maximilian Bercovicz, Patrick
Goldberg were already spoken for.

30:49.590 --> 30:53.890
And they were up in
a very fancy cemetery in Riverdale.

30:57.140 --> 30:59.310
What's this all mean?

30:59.520 --> 31:01.310
It means...

31:03.440 --> 31:08.490
..."Noodles, though you've been
hiding in the asshole of
the world, we found you.

31:08.650 --> 31:10.570
We know where you are."

31:11.280 --> 31:13.160
It means...

31:14.030 --> 31:15.330
..."Get ready."

31:17.950 --> 31:19.250
For what?

31:22.670 --> 31:25.460
That's the one thing it didn't say.

31:26.460 --> 31:28.300
(Sighs)

31:54.490 --> 31:56.530
What do you think?

31:56.700 --> 32:00.830
I think the answer's here.
That's why I came back.

32:03.960 --> 32:06.170
Hm.

32:19.850 --> 32:22.810
I moved everything in here.

32:27.020 --> 32:30.690
I had to sell the house, the backroom.

32:31.990 --> 32:36.870
You know, I always thought you
might have helped yourself
to that million bucks.

32:37.030 --> 32:39.200
But now I know.

32:40.330 --> 32:42.120
No.

32:43.670 --> 32:46.330
You're on your ass worse than ever.

32:47.920 --> 32:50.210
But I thought it was you who... 

32:50.380 --> 32:52.760
No, you thought wrong.

32:54.840 --> 32:57.390
The suitcase was empty.

32:59.760 --> 33:02.140
Then who took it?

33:06.400 --> 33:10.270
That's what I've been asking myself
for 35 years.

33:21.870 --> 33:24.790
If it bothers you, I can sleep here.

33:24.960 --> 33:29.080
- You can have my room.
- No. It's okay.

33:29.250 --> 33:32.090
(Siren Wailing)

33:48.900 --> 33:52.610
- How's your sister?
- I haven't seen her for years.

33:53.320 --> 33:55.780
She's a big star now.

33:57.990 --> 34:00.490
We should have known, huh?

34:01.330 --> 34:04.830
You can always tell the winners
at the starting gate.

34:05.580 --> 34:09.500
You can always tell the winners,
and you can tell the losers.

34:11.130 --> 34:13.500
Who would've put a penny on you?

34:15.510 --> 34:18.429
I'd have put everything
I ever had on you.

34:21.469 --> 34:23.760
Yeah, and you would've lost.

34:35.780 --> 34:40.110
Well, you're beat. Good night.

34:40.280 --> 34:42.989
Good night, Moe. Thanks.

34:48.370 --> 34:51.370
What have you been doing
all these years?

34:55.250 --> 34:57.380
Been going to bed early.

37:41.920 --> 37:45.510
[ Joseph LaCalle - AMAPOLA Playing ]

38:03.690 --> 38:05.320
(Gasps)

39:47.130 --> 39:49.670
Deborah, Papa says you should help.

39:50.130 --> 39:51.470
No.

39:51.800 --> 39:55.010
We've got customers all over.
We can't do everything.

39:55.180 --> 39:58.850
Try. I've got my elocution lessons.

40:06.610 --> 40:08.610
[ Music Stops ]

40:49.690 --> 40:54.200
Fat, you better spray the toilet.
I saw a cockroach in there.

41:02.960 --> 41:05.330
(Sighing)

41:10.710 --> 41:11.710
[Noodles]
Sorry.

41:11.880 --> 41:13.470
[Man Shouts In Yiddish]

41:19.930 --> 41:22.020
[Deborah] Sorry, I can't make it today.
See you tomorrow.

41:22.180 --> 41:24.180
- [Girl] Okay. Bye.
- [Deborah] Bye.

41:28.310 --> 41:29.900
(Fats Grunts)

41:30.070 --> 41:32.150
[Woman Shouts In Yiddish]

41:32.400 --> 41:34.190
Sorry, Fats.

41:41.580 --> 41:43.910
- [Patsy] Noodles!
- [Dominic] Bugsy's got a job for us.

41:44.080 --> 41:46.080
[Patsy]
Hurry up. He don't wait.

41:46.290 --> 41:48.290
(Chattering)

42:19.820 --> 42:21.780
[Noodles]
Who you calling a cockroach?

42:21.950 --> 42:25.120
So, what are you?
You're filthy, you make me sick.

42:25.290 --> 42:29.460
You crawl up toilet walls
just like a roach. So, what are you?

42:29.630 --> 42:31.170
Let go!

42:31.340 --> 42:35.300
I make you sick, huh? Then how
come you showed me your tush?

42:35.550 --> 42:37.840
Hm. To a roach.

42:41.220 --> 42:44.810
Go look at yourself, David Aaronson.

42:59.660 --> 43:03.620
She don't leave me alone, I'm going to
give her what she's asking for.

43:03.780 --> 43:06.330
- What's Bugsy want?
- We got to wake up a deadbeat.

43:06.500 --> 43:09.620
That schmuck at the newsstand didn't pay.

43:58.880 --> 44:00.840
[Noodles]
Here's your money, sir.

44:12.060 --> 44:15.440
(Man Yelling)

44:21.110 --> 44:23.110
[Noodles]
It's beautiful.

44:27.160 --> 44:30.450
- [Dominic] Ha-ha-ha.
- Look at it, it looks great! Wow!

44:30.750 --> 44:33.750
[Man Screaming And Sobbing]

44:38.420 --> 44:40.510
[Noodles]
Come on, guys.

44:48.430 --> 44:50.890
Come on, come on.

44:51.600 --> 44:53.850
Now make up your mind.

44:54.230 --> 44:57.650
- Noodles, let's take the dollar.
- Yeah.

44:57.860 --> 45:00.360
[Man]
Skip, here you go.

45:02.440 --> 45:03.990
[Noodles]
That one.

45:04.990 --> 45:06.240
Him.

45:06.490 --> 45:08.990
[Man]
Hey, Sam, I'll see you next Thursday.

45:09.450 --> 45:13.080
- [Noodles] That one.
- [Man] Hey, and bring your wife along.

45:14.420 --> 45:15.460
Are you nuts?

45:15.620 --> 45:19.840
Bugsy said we could take the dollar
or we could roll the drunk.

45:20.000 --> 45:22.300
Yeah, but he isn't even drunk yet.

45:23.010 --> 45:24.510
We'll wait.

45:27.510 --> 45:32.310
- Well, you roll that one over there.
- What's to roll? He drunk it all.

45:37.190 --> 45:39.270
Bounce that little shikker.

45:43.610 --> 45:47.410
[Shouting In Yiddish]

45:59.840 --> 46:03.710
[ Playing Flute ]

46:12.060 --> 46:15.060
(Boys Whistling)

46:28.360 --> 46:29.740
Jacket.

46:38.540 --> 46:39.830
[Speaking Indistinctly]

46:40.000 --> 46:41.960
It's Fartface.

46:45.590 --> 46:46.880
Shit!

46:48.760 --> 46:50.680
We should've took the dollar.

46:50.840 --> 46:54.720
Could've had 10 hot corned-beef
sandwiches on poppy-seed rolls.

47:06.740 --> 47:12.240
Look, the wagon will hide us
from Fartface. Get ready!

47:41.850 --> 47:43.650
Now! Throw your jacket over him.

47:45.820 --> 47:50.650
[Max] Hey, mister, you sick?
Aw, poor guy, you'll be okay.
Come on, I'll help you.

47:50.820 --> 47:53.660
Come on, up you go.

47:53.820 --> 47:56.490
Now, you're worse
than my Uncle Nathan.

47:56.660 --> 48:00.120
Why do you want to get soused?
You can't even walk. I'll take you home.

48:00.290 --> 48:02.120
Go, Mama.

48:11.050 --> 48:14.340
[Whitey] Stop right there. Hey, you!
Yeah, I'm talking to you.

48:15.680 --> 48:17.850
What the hell are you kids doing here?

48:18.060 --> 48:21.850
- What are we kids doing here?
- We're getting it up the ass.

48:22.350 --> 48:25.650
Yeah, getting screwed.
Is there a law against it?

48:25.810 --> 48:29.780
[Dominic] Can you spare a dime for
pisherkehs that just got it up the ass?

48:29.940 --> 48:32.700
Come on, get out of here.
Come on, get off the street.

48:32.860 --> 48:35.280
Go on, get out of here.
Get off the street.

48:35.450 --> 48:37.660
Go ahead. And don't come back.

48:37.830 --> 48:41.660
I don't want to ever see you here again.
All right?

48:43.000 --> 48:44.870
[ Playing Flute ]

49:13.990 --> 49:17.110
Hey, stop by for you later.

49:19.370 --> 49:21.870
Yeah, but knock here on the john first.

49:23.660 --> 49:28.750
My old man's praying, and my old lady's
crying. And the light's turned off.

49:29.040 --> 49:33.550
What the hell should I go home for?
At least in here I can read.

50:36.280 --> 50:39.490
- [Mother] Where are you going?
- [Peggy] Mama, don't get worked up.

50:39.700 --> 50:41.620
[Mother]
You got pots to clean.

50:46.460 --> 50:48.080
Peggeleh?

50:48.250 --> 50:51.250
[Peggy] I'll be right back, Ma.
I got to go to the can.

50:58.720 --> 51:00.180
Hi, Peggy.

51:00.340 --> 51:02.970
At least you could lock the door.

51:06.310 --> 51:07.850
Don't you like it?

51:15.480 --> 51:16.730
I've seen better.

51:17.490 --> 51:19.820
- You seen lots?
- How many you seen?

51:20.490 --> 51:23.160
I'll tell you how many. None.

51:27.950 --> 51:29.500
Let me see yours.

51:44.050 --> 51:46.680
Looksies, no feelsies.

51:49.560 --> 51:53.650
Peggy. Peggy, I... I... I... 

51:55.070 --> 51:56.520
I want... 

51:56.980 --> 51:59.860
- You like it, don't you?
- Not for free, I don't.

52:00.070 --> 52:04.280
You bring me a Charlotte Russe
with whipped cream, then you
can do anything you like.

52:04.490 --> 52:07.240
Tomorrow. I'll bring it to you tomorrow.

52:07.410 --> 52:10.410
- I'll bring it tomorrow.
- Look, I don't give credit.

52:10.580 --> 52:12.080
I promise. I promise.

52:12.290 --> 52:16.420
You better stop squeezing me,
or I'm going to poop in my pants.

52:16.920 --> 52:18.960
(Sighs)

52:22.930 --> 52:24.260
Well, are you getting out?

52:43.660 --> 52:45.660
[Speaking In Yiddish]

53:12.770 --> 53:15.230
Come on, come on.

53:42.460 --> 53:44.630
Give me six copies.

53:46.180 --> 53:49.300
Drop your pants
and I'll stick it to you again.

53:53.390 --> 53:56.690
- What do you mean, "again"?
- That's a long story.

53:56.900 --> 53:59.690
And look what time it is.

54:00.110 --> 54:04.190
It's already 6:34. And I got to go.

54:04.360 --> 54:05.530
(Max Sighs)

54:05.700 --> 54:07.860
Boy, I got a lot of work to do.

54:08.030 --> 54:09.990
Hold it a minute.

54:10.160 --> 54:14.830
Now it's 6:35.
And I haven't got a damn thing to do.

54:15.210 --> 54:19.040
Just you wait, asshole.
I'll do something with your time.

54:19.210 --> 54:20.540
Wait! Hey!

54:20.710 --> 54:23.000
Since we're talking about time...

54:23.170 --> 54:26.920
...it looks like you're going to break
that lamp at 6:36.

54:28.300 --> 54:29.840
- Where did you pinch this?
- It's mine.

54:30.010 --> 54:32.640
- Prove it.
- I gave it to him.

54:33.470 --> 54:35.140
[Whitey]
Oh, yeah?

54:35.930 --> 54:37.730
Who the hell are you?

54:38.480 --> 54:41.150
- Where you from?
- The Bronx.

54:41.730 --> 54:44.020
And you give away watches?

54:44.570 --> 54:46.530
He's my uncle.

54:47.070 --> 54:49.740
- And who gave it to you?
- My Uncle Nathan.

54:50.370 --> 54:52.200
My little brother.

54:52.700 --> 54:55.830
Tell your uncle
to stop by the precinct.

54:56.000 --> 54:57.870
- [Max] He's dead.
- Alcoholic.

54:58.040 --> 55:00.040
[Max]
In Kishnev, Poland.

55:02.750 --> 55:04.340
Hm.

55:05.050 --> 55:08.010
Then he don't need it no more.
It's been requisitioned.

55:08.340 --> 55:14.050
- Requi... What's that mean?
- Pinched, by him. At 6:37.

55:14.220 --> 55:17.390
Just remember, I got my eye on you two.

55:17.560 --> 55:19.770
I got my eye on you too.

55:19.980 --> 55:24.610
Take it! Take it!
Take the lamp off. I can't hold it.

55:25.900 --> 55:27.650
Max.

55:31.530 --> 55:33.240
Who's this?

55:35.290 --> 55:37.040
[Max]
My uncle.

55:56.930 --> 56:00.640
- That one. With the cream.
- The 5-cent one?

56:01.020 --> 56:02.480
[Patsy]
Yeah.

56:02.650 --> 56:07.110
For the twopenny one she only gives
you a hand job. I can do that myself.

56:08.610 --> 56:09.650
Not that one!

56:10.240 --> 56:11.820
That one.

56:12.820 --> 56:14.280
You sure?

56:15.280 --> 56:17.330
Wrap it up pretty.

56:56.950 --> 56:59.790
Good morning. Peggy home?

56:59.950 --> 57:01.870
[Mother]
She's taking a bath.

57:02.080 --> 57:04.670
That's great.
Would you tell her I'm here?

57:04.830 --> 57:08.290
Hey, Ma. Another bucket of water.

57:09.590 --> 57:11.460
Wait.

59:37.990 --> 59:39.650
(Door Opens)

59:40.990 --> 59:43.820
- [Peggy] What do you want?
- Me?

59:44.370 --> 59:49.370
- Mama said you were looking for me.
- Oh, ye... No. The guys told me that... 

59:49.540 --> 59:53.750
- What?
- I'll come back some other time.

01:00:28.700 --> 01:00:30.660
Noodles!

01:00:32.790 --> 01:00:35.420
Noodles! Noodles! Noodles!

01:00:35.880 --> 01:00:37.880
(Man Moaning)

01:00:38.050 --> 01:00:40.050
(Peggy Panting)

01:00:41.010 --> 01:00:42.130
[Whitey]
What?

01:00:42.300 --> 01:00:43.720
[Noodles]
Did you get it?

01:00:43.890 --> 01:00:48.600
His asshole blinked, but we got him.
Nice going, Fartface. And on duty too.

01:00:48.890 --> 01:00:53.440
Heh. Uh, ha, ha. You boys caught me
with my pants down that time. Heh, heh.

01:00:53.600 --> 01:00:56.690
No, we caught you with your schmuck
up the tuchus of a minor.

01:00:56.860 --> 01:01:00.730
- Scram. Put this someplace safe.
- [Whitey] That's all right.
Ha, ha. Hey, hold it!

01:01:00.900 --> 01:01:03.200
Where you going?
Stop! Hold it! Wait a minute!

01:01:03.360 --> 01:01:05.110
Hey, you, stop! Hold it.

01:01:05.320 --> 01:01:10.290
- What are you going to
do with that plate?
- It depends. What time is it, Max?

01:01:10.450 --> 01:01:13.410
I think it's time we got our watch back.

01:01:13.580 --> 01:01:14.580
(Chuckles)

01:01:14.750 --> 01:01:17.380
- Okay, boys, we're even.
- The hell we are.

01:01:17.540 --> 01:01:19.960
You'll be collecting your
pension before we're even.

01:01:20.130 --> 01:01:21.760
[Peggy]
Hiya, fellas.

01:01:22.760 --> 01:01:24.420
What do you boys want?

01:01:24.590 --> 01:01:26.930
[Max]
First off...

01:01:27.140 --> 01:01:29.260
- ...you're paying Peggy for us.
- [Peggy] Ha, ha.

01:01:29.430 --> 01:01:31.560
Okay. That's it?

01:01:31.930 --> 01:01:33.390
[Max]
Go ahead while I tell him.

01:01:33.560 --> 01:01:37.600
[Noodles] Ha-ha-ha. I can't believe it.
My first time, and a lousy
cop's paying for it.

01:01:37.770 --> 01:01:39.440
(Peggy & Noodles Laugh)

01:01:40.070 --> 01:01:44.280
[Whitey] Look, what else do you kids
want for that plate? Huh?

01:01:44.450 --> 01:01:47.490
Noodles was telling me
about a guy called Bugsy.

01:01:47.660 --> 01:01:50.490
Seems he's boss of this neighborhood,
thanks to you.

01:01:50.660 --> 01:01:53.790
- Meaning what?
- Meaning he pays you off.

01:01:53.960 --> 01:01:57.670
[Peggy] Will you slow down?
What is your hurry? Take it easy.

01:01:57.880 --> 01:02:00.960
If you keep this up,
you're going to come too fast.

01:02:01.130 --> 01:02:02.170
(Noodles Moans)

01:02:02.380 --> 01:02:06.680
[Peggy] Do you see what I mean?
You're so stupid. I can't believe it.

01:02:06.930 --> 01:02:12.180
So why does Bugsy pay you?
What do you do for him?

01:02:13.470 --> 01:02:17.640
- I close an eye once in a while.
- Well, now you close an eye for us.

01:02:17.810 --> 01:02:21.020
Why? What are you kids up to?

01:02:24.900 --> 01:02:26.360
He'll tell you.

01:02:26.530 --> 01:02:30.120
Me, him, Cockeye and Patsy,
we're working together.

01:02:30.280 --> 01:02:31.320
(Laughs)

01:02:31.490 --> 01:02:32.830
Bugsy'll flatten you.

01:02:32.990 --> 01:02:36.330
And besides... I don't put up with
no trouble on my beat.

01:02:36.500 --> 01:02:40.630
You'll put up, and you'll shut up.
You hear nothing, and you see nothing.

01:02:40.790 --> 01:02:42.670
Just like you did for Bugsy.

01:02:42.840 --> 01:02:44.210
[Max]
Shit!

01:02:44.460 --> 01:02:49.510
Aw, don't get upset. That makes it worse.
It can happen the first time.

01:02:49.680 --> 01:02:54.140
- It's them two talking out there.
- Can't you see you're ruining the mood?

01:02:54.310 --> 01:02:56.640
We made our deal.

01:02:57.230 --> 01:03:00.940
- So take a walk.
- [Peggy] Come here, honey.

01:03:02.940 --> 01:03:06.740
- Feel good, bubeleh?
- Ha! He'll never get it up.

01:03:08.070 --> 01:03:12.490
[Peggy]
Relax. Okay. Calm down, calm down.

01:03:12.660 --> 01:03:15.700
(Peggy Laughing)

01:03:18.040 --> 01:03:22.710
Okay. Okay, come here.

01:03:30.840 --> 01:03:34.890
(Peggy Moaning)

01:03:47.860 --> 01:03:49.860
(Car Horn Honks)

01:04:42.460 --> 01:04:44.290
[Deborah]
I'm glad the baby's better.

01:04:44.580 --> 01:04:48.920
- [Becky] Happy Pesach, Deborah.
- [Deborah] Happy Pesach, Becky.

01:04:54.930 --> 01:04:57.350
Hurry. We're going to be late.

01:04:57.560 --> 01:05:00.350
- Oh, there's Deborah.
- Sorry I'm late. Mama needed help.

01:05:00.560 --> 01:05:05.440
Good girl. I just locked up,
and I'm giving you the keys.

01:05:18.330 --> 01:05:22.450
I thought I'd just practice my dance
routines. That's all. All right?

01:05:22.620 --> 01:05:25.830
Debbeleh, make sure you
don't let the goyim in.

01:05:26.830 --> 01:05:30.500
- Okay, bye.
- See you later, Debbie. Bye.

01:05:33.880 --> 01:05:36.180
(Whistling)

01:06:18.140 --> 01:06:22.180
[ Joseph LaCalle - AMAPOLA Playing ]

01:06:43.080 --> 01:06:45.450
[Deborah]
Get down off of there, roach.

01:06:45.660 --> 01:06:47.410
That record is just like Ex-Lax.

01:06:47.580 --> 01:06:51.290
Every time I put it on,
you have to go to the bathroom.

01:07:08.810 --> 01:07:10.440
What are you doing?

01:07:10.600 --> 01:07:13.440
- Give me a drink.
- We're closed.

01:07:13.610 --> 01:07:18.150
Nice people don't drink on Pesach.
They go to the synagogue.

01:07:18.320 --> 01:07:20.320
So, what are you doing here?

01:07:20.490 --> 01:07:23.280
Somebody has got to keep an eye
on the place.

01:07:23.450 --> 01:07:27.660
There are a lot of little thieves out there.
One of them could get into your house.

01:07:27.830 --> 01:07:31.000
Especially if you leave the door open.

01:08:03.320 --> 01:08:06.160
You can pray here too.

01:08:07.370 --> 01:08:11.250
Here or in the synagogue,
to God it's the same difference.

01:08:12.830 --> 01:08:15.040
Come over here and sit down.

01:08:48.160 --> 01:08:51.040
"My beloved is white and ruddy.

01:08:51.210 --> 01:08:54.830
His skin is as the most fine gold.

01:08:55.000 --> 01:08:59.050
His cheeks are as a bed of spices."

01:09:01.800 --> 01:09:05.590
Even though he hasn't washed
since last December.

01:09:09.890 --> 01:09:12.850
"His eyes are as the eyes of doves.

01:09:13.020 --> 01:09:15.729
His body is as bright ivory.

01:09:15.899 --> 01:09:19.819
His legs are as pillars of marble."

01:09:21.689 --> 01:09:24.569
In pants so dirty
they stand by themselves.

01:09:26.370 --> 01:09:29.580
"He is altogether lovable."

01:09:31.120 --> 01:09:33.710
But he'll always be a two-bit punk...

01:09:33.870 --> 01:09:38.750
...so he'll never be my beloved.
What a shame.

01:10:06.360 --> 01:10:08.620
(Door Knob Rattling)

01:10:09.030 --> 01:10:10.070
(Deborah Gasps)

01:10:10.240 --> 01:10:11.950
Somebody is there.

01:10:24.590 --> 01:10:26.170
There is nobody.

01:10:26.340 --> 01:10:28.180
(Whistling)

01:10:32.970 --> 01:10:34.140
It's Max.

01:10:34.390 --> 01:10:37.520
Ah. So that's who it was.

01:10:38.190 --> 01:10:39.810
[Max]
Noodles!

01:10:44.150 --> 01:10:46.820
Go on, run.
Your mother's calling you.

01:10:52.950 --> 01:10:54.330
[Max]
Noodles!

01:10:55.500 --> 01:10:58.000
Just going to go see what he wants.

01:11:15.020 --> 01:11:17.310
(Whistling)

01:11:27.190 --> 01:11:29.990
- [Noodles] Hey.
- Yo.

01:11:32.870 --> 01:11:36.080
- You been here long?
- No.

01:11:37.200 --> 01:11:39.460
Were you in there?

01:11:41.830 --> 01:11:44.040
You're one lousy kisser.

01:11:44.210 --> 01:11:47.380
I seen you go in there
after that ball-buster.

01:11:47.550 --> 01:11:52.550
Here's the stuff from last night.
We got four for the silverware,
six for the typewriter.

01:11:52.760 --> 01:11:56.970
Shitsy Lipschitz wouldn't cough up
any more. We got to get somebody else.

01:11:59.270 --> 01:12:01.890
I came to divvy up.

01:12:02.400 --> 01:12:07.030
- Tomorrow, with the others.
- I also came to pick you up.

01:12:08.490 --> 01:12:12.530
- I can't come right now.
- The houses, the stores are all empty.

01:12:12.700 --> 01:12:15.910
We got our pick. You pick that.

01:12:16.790 --> 01:12:18.750
Yeah.

01:12:21.790 --> 01:12:24.960
Some partner I got. Have fun.

01:12:32.130 --> 01:12:34.260
[Man]
How's it going, boys?

01:12:34.430 --> 01:12:36.600
Who's that?

01:12:37.010 --> 01:12:38.930
Bugsy.

01:12:56.240 --> 01:12:59.660
I hear you guys are in business
for yourselves now, huh?

01:12:59.830 --> 01:13:01.790
I hear you are doing real good.

01:13:02.660 --> 01:13:03.710
(Grunts)

01:13:08.960 --> 01:13:10.880
Aren't you going to introduce me
to your friend here?

01:13:11.050 --> 01:13:12.420
(Noodles Grunting)

01:13:14.680 --> 01:13:17.260
I'll introduce myself.

01:13:22.140 --> 01:13:24.060
Excuse the glove.

01:13:24.850 --> 01:13:25.850
(Grunts)

01:13:26.020 --> 01:13:28.610
(Noodles Groaning)

01:13:32.610 --> 01:13:33.650
Ow!

01:13:33.820 --> 01:13:35.360
[Boy]
Son of a bitch!

01:13:36.950 --> 01:13:38.570
(Groaning)

01:13:40.160 --> 01:13:41.540
(Bottles Shattering)

01:13:55.010 --> 01:13:56.300
(Coughing)

01:14:22.830 --> 01:14:24.750
That's my cut.

01:14:25.120 --> 01:14:29.080
You don't work for me,
you don't work for no one.

01:14:29.250 --> 01:14:31.040
- I don't like bosses.
- [Bugsy] Ha, ha.

01:14:31.550 --> 01:14:35.050
You was better off
you stayed in the Bronx.

01:14:38.260 --> 01:14:41.260
It would have been better for you too.

01:14:48.940 --> 01:14:51.560
(Bugsy Spits)

01:15:07.040 --> 01:15:08.540
(Max Coughing)

01:15:08.750 --> 01:15:11.580
(Noodles Groaning)

01:15:23.310 --> 01:15:27.480
- I'm going to kill him one of these days.
- Yeah?

01:15:27.940 --> 01:15:32.440
Meantime it looks like he's killed us.

01:15:49.710 --> 01:15:51.540
(Knocking)

01:15:51.710 --> 01:15:54.500
Deborah, open up the door.

01:15:55.710 --> 01:15:58.710
Deborah, open up the door.

01:16:00.220 --> 01:16:01.800
Deborah.

01:16:03.510 --> 01:16:05.510
[Inaudible Dialogue]

01:16:43.840 --> 01:16:47.680
- [Al] That stuff,
is it ready for the club?
- We're loading it.

01:16:56.690 --> 01:16:58.360
(Men Laughing And Chattering)

01:17:22.300 --> 01:17:27.050
- [Al] Eh. Che cazzo succede down here?
- Al, we got the big boys with us today.

01:17:27.220 --> 01:17:30.930
- They want to work for us.
- Doing what Bugsy did. We want his job.

01:17:31.100 --> 01:17:32.270
[Fred]
Do you get that? Ha, ha.

01:17:32.430 --> 01:17:37.810
[In Italian Accent] We the best escorts
you ever going to get.

01:17:38.610 --> 01:17:41.530
A fangulo a ma, escort your
mother's ass out of here.

01:17:41.690 --> 01:17:42.740
(Fred Chuckles)

01:17:42.900 --> 01:17:48.120
Okay. Let's go, Noodles. We'll peddle
your invention somewhere else, huh?

01:17:49.910 --> 01:17:51.950
[Fred]
Hey, wait a minute.

01:17:53.830 --> 01:17:54.870
What invention?

01:17:55.040 --> 01:17:57.960
- You ship your stuff by
the river, right?
- Si, sometimes.

01:17:58.130 --> 01:18:01.710
And when you get caught by the Coast
Guard, you throw all the cases overboard.

01:18:01.880 --> 01:18:04.590
- You lose the whole shipment.
- [Al] So?

01:18:04.760 --> 01:18:07.470
For 10 percent,
we'll save it all for you.

01:18:07.640 --> 01:18:10.430
- What do you got, a submarine?
- We got salt.

01:18:11.890 --> 01:18:13.430
You got what?

01:18:13.600 --> 01:18:18.440
- Salt. Me and the boys are rolling salts.
- Yeah. We need 3 tons of
salt per shipment.

01:18:18.610 --> 01:18:22.150
Get the fuck out of here.
Go back to school where you belong.

01:18:22.610 --> 01:18:25.110
What is it with all this salt?

01:18:25.280 --> 01:18:29.780
Hey, hey, we got salt on our Noodles.
Show them.

01:18:42.500 --> 01:18:44.460
[Noodles]
This is full of salt.

01:18:49.470 --> 01:18:51.100
All right, come here.

01:19:06.190 --> 01:19:08.860
- [Al] So?
- Keep your shirt on, Capuano.

01:19:09.030 --> 01:19:11.660
[Noodles] We got to wait for the salt
to dissolve.

01:19:15.540 --> 01:19:18.500
(Horn Blaring)

01:19:43.860 --> 01:19:46.820
- Well?
- Hey, what's wrong?

01:19:52.950 --> 01:19:54.030
Hey, look.

01:19:54.200 --> 01:19:56.370
[Dominic]
Hey. Wow!

01:19:58.540 --> 01:19:59.870
[Patsy]
Great!

01:20:01.370 --> 01:20:03.880
- Look at that!
- It's great.

01:20:04.040 --> 01:20:05.460
- Noodles.
- Look at it.

01:20:07.090 --> 01:20:10.010
- [Noodles] I see them!
What did I tell you?
- Yeah.

01:20:14.100 --> 01:20:15.390
Yeah!

01:20:16.060 --> 01:20:20.390
(Laughing And Chattering)

01:20:24.060 --> 01:20:28.730
- [Patsy] Hey, Noodles.
- [Noodles] Hooray. Hooray for us!

01:20:32.610 --> 01:20:33.910
We did it.

01:20:35.080 --> 01:20:36.530
Come here, Max.

01:20:38.040 --> 01:20:41.290
- [Max] We did it.
- [Noodles] No, Max, no!

01:20:45.090 --> 01:20:46.290
Max.

01:20:48.000 --> 01:20:49.420
Max.

01:21:01.100 --> 01:21:02.430
Max!

01:21:05.020 --> 01:21:06.270
Max!

01:21:20.660 --> 01:21:23.040
What would you do without me?

01:21:24.670 --> 01:21:27.960
(All Laughing)

01:22:28.650 --> 01:22:29.900
[Max]
There.

01:22:33.230 --> 01:22:36.530
From here on, we establish
the shared funds of the gang.

01:22:36.700 --> 01:22:39.700
They belong to all of us together
and to none of us alone.

01:22:39.870 --> 01:22:45.200
And we solemnly swear to put in 50
percent of everything we make. Agreed?

01:22:45.370 --> 01:22:46.620
Agreed.

01:22:46.920 --> 01:22:48.710
- [Patsy] Agreed.
- [Cockeye] Agreed.

01:22:51.880 --> 01:22:53.500
Agreed.

01:22:55.630 --> 01:22:57.550
I want to take another peek.

01:23:17.240 --> 01:23:19.070
[Man]
Announcing the immediate departure...

01:23:19.240 --> 01:23:23.910
...of the Lackawanna Railroad,
Hudson Valley Express, Poughkeepsie...

01:23:24.080 --> 01:23:29.040
...Albany, Utica and Buffalo.

01:23:30.460 --> 01:23:32.540
All aboard.

01:23:36.090 --> 01:23:39.760
This goes to Fat Moe.
We don't tell him what it's for.

01:23:39.930 --> 01:23:43.260
And he gives it back
only when we're all together.

01:23:43.430 --> 01:23:44.680
Agreed?

01:23:45.770 --> 01:23:47.770
[All]
Agreed.

01:23:50.900 --> 01:23:52.270
Agreed.

01:24:06.490 --> 01:24:08.450
[ Playing Flute ]

01:24:49.870 --> 01:24:51.870
[Dominic]
Bugsy's coming! Run!

01:25:09.270 --> 01:25:10.350
(Gunshot)

01:25:43.680 --> 01:25:45.630
Noodles.

01:25:46.550 --> 01:25:48.600
I slipped.

01:27:26.690 --> 01:27:30.110
- [Noodles] Bastard!
- Aah!

01:27:30.280 --> 01:27:32.450
[Noodles]
Yentzer. Schmuck.

01:27:33.330 --> 01:27:35.330
(Both Grunting)

01:27:39.500 --> 01:27:40.540
(Horses Galloping)

01:27:47.840 --> 01:27:49.680
(Grunts)

01:27:49.840 --> 01:27:51.430
(Officer Groaning)

01:27:54.180 --> 01:27:56.680
(Noodles Yells Then Groaning)

01:28:19.000 --> 01:28:21.460
(Bell Ringing)

01:29:20.480 --> 01:29:23.270
(Doors Close)

01:29:23.440 --> 01:29:26.690
(Locks Clicking)

01:29:47.460 --> 01:29:49.040
Want to go in?

01:29:52.970 --> 01:29:54.340
Yeah.

01:29:54.800 --> 01:29:56.760
You a relative?

01:30:00.060 --> 01:30:01.310
An uncle.

01:30:13.860 --> 01:30:15.490
It's open.

01:30:16.320 --> 01:30:19.370
(Plane Passes)

01:33:05.530 --> 01:33:07.990
(Key Clanging)

01:33:27.260 --> 01:33:30.680
[Noodles] "Erected to their everlasting
memory by their friend and brother...

01:33:30.850 --> 01:33:33.270
...David Aaronson, 1967."

01:35:09.990 --> 01:35:13.240
(Siren Wailing)

01:35:25.720 --> 01:35:27.720
(Honks Horn)

01:35:43.320 --> 01:35:46.320
(Metallic Clanging)

01:36:13.140 --> 01:36:15.350
[Man]
Can I take that for you, sir?

01:36:17.810 --> 01:36:19.850
Your limousine is waiting.

01:36:30.240 --> 01:36:31.950
Maxie.

01:36:43.540 --> 01:36:46.540
How are you, uncle?
You're looking good.

01:36:48.010 --> 01:36:49.760
You're looking a little better.

01:36:53.340 --> 01:36:57.260
Come on. Better get
you off the streets.

01:37:00.520 --> 01:37:03.770
- Some limousine.
- Ha, ha. What are you talking, huh?

01:37:04.060 --> 01:37:08.690
We own the company now. It's
a good cover. You'd be
surprised. It pays off too.

01:37:08.860 --> 01:37:12.740
My mother wrote me you was
in the body snatching business.

01:37:15.070 --> 01:37:18.280
By the way, I appreciate
everything you did for my family.

01:37:18.540 --> 01:37:20.750
Forget it. It's your dough.

01:37:21.410 --> 01:37:24.750
It's all down in black and white
in the company books.

01:37:25.580 --> 01:37:29.920
You're the company. You and Patsy and
Cockeye. Gravediggers and equal partners.

01:37:30.090 --> 01:37:34.300
Heh. Hey, enough of this, huh?
Business before pleasure.

01:37:35.140 --> 01:37:37.260
We got a rush job. Here.

01:37:40.100 --> 01:37:43.140
Come here. Look at this. Come here.

01:37:44.770 --> 01:37:48.520
Sudden death. Fucking tragedy, huh?

01:37:49.820 --> 01:37:53.150
- Twenty-six years old.
- Twenty-six?

01:37:53.900 --> 01:37:54.950
[Speaks In Yiddish]

01:37:55.110 --> 01:37:59.160
- [In English] What a shame!
- Great stiff. She died of an overdose.

01:37:59.330 --> 01:38:01.330
And I'm ready for another. Ha-ha-ha.

01:38:01.540 --> 01:38:05.040
Come on, Noodles. Pump the life
into her. You didn't turn pansy
in there, did you?

01:38:08.750 --> 01:38:09.840
[Max]
There you go.

01:38:10.000 --> 01:38:12.300
(Woman Moaning And Laughing)

01:38:13.130 --> 01:38:17.180
Turning over in the grave.
They do it every time.

01:38:58.180 --> 01:39:01.010
[Woman]
Ha, ha. Don't worry. A pansy he isn't.

01:39:01.180 --> 01:39:03.310
(Max Laughs)

01:39:04.020 --> 01:39:06.520
- [Noodles] Thanks.
- [Max] You're welcome, Noodles.

01:39:07.190 --> 01:39:08.980
Whoops. Uh, sorry.

01:39:09.310 --> 01:39:11.480
[Woman]
Thanks. Good night.

