I'd take it easy.

02:57:07.700 --> 02:57:10.070
[Max]
We'll take it easy when we got 20.

02:57:11.450 --> 02:57:14.780
- Fifty.
- [Noodles] Where you going to get that?

02:57:18.120 --> 02:57:19.790
[Max]
Right here.

02:57:29.130 --> 02:57:30.880
What's that?

02:57:34.310 --> 02:57:36.220
It's a dream.

02:57:38.640 --> 02:57:41.390
A dream I've been dreaming
all my life.

02:57:41.560 --> 02:57:45.690
I swear to God, Noodles, you and me
together, we can make it come true.

02:57:49.610 --> 02:57:50.820
What is it?

02:57:56.120 --> 02:57:57.950
The Federal Reserve Bank.

02:58:01.670 --> 02:58:05.130
It's the biggest step
we can take, Noodles.

02:58:28.190 --> 02:58:30.030
You're really crazy.

02:58:31.240 --> 02:58:35.910
Don't you ever say that to me.
Don't you ever say that to me again!

03:00:00.490 --> 03:00:01.490
(Sighs)

03:00:01.660 --> 03:00:06.540
What chance is there that a crazy
thing like this might succeed, hm?

03:00:07.750 --> 03:00:09.670
Don't ask me, ask Max.

03:00:10.090 --> 03:00:15.920
You know as well as I do that this is
suicide, pure and simple, for everyone.

03:00:16.680 --> 03:00:22.100
Yeah, well, don't tell me, tell him.
You got your own methods.

03:00:22.720 --> 03:00:24.890
Yeah, I tried.

03:00:25.350 --> 03:00:28.440
He doesn't want to screw anymore.

03:00:31.400 --> 03:00:34.730
All he thinks about is this job.

03:00:37.240 --> 03:00:40.320
Tear gas, hostages,
now he's going to do this...

03:00:40.490 --> 03:00:43.910
He's going to do it with or without you.

03:00:49.170 --> 03:00:52.590
Noodles, we've never liked each other.

03:00:56.880 --> 03:01:02.510
We put up with each other
for Max's sake. So why don't
we just get together once...

03:01:02.680 --> 03:01:05.430
...and do something for him?

03:01:15.150 --> 03:01:17.110
And after that...

03:01:18.150 --> 03:01:21.320
...we can go back to being enemies.

03:01:29.830 --> 03:01:34.880
You know... if you were
all in jail first...

03:01:35.050 --> 03:01:38.130
...there wouldn't be any bank job.

03:01:49.690 --> 03:01:52.350
I got the idea from your friend Max.

03:01:54.190 --> 03:01:55.400
What do you mean?

03:01:56.150 --> 03:01:58.320
(Chuckling)

03:01:58.490 --> 03:02:01.820
He laughs at you. He makes fun of you.

03:02:03.660 --> 03:02:06.950
He says Eve has got you by the balls.

03:02:07.120 --> 03:02:11.040
Every time you walk past this place,
you shit in your pants.

03:02:11.210 --> 03:02:15.000
You'd do anything for the cops
to pick you up so you
wouldn't have to do this job.

03:02:15.170 --> 03:02:17.250
Is that true, huh?

03:02:29.980 --> 03:02:31.560
Well, then do it.

03:02:31.730 --> 03:02:35.020
Do it. Put him in jail.
Put him in jail. Not long.

03:02:35.190 --> 03:02:39.070
Just long enough so that he can
get the idea out of his mind.

03:02:40.860 --> 03:02:45.990
If you can't stand being away
from him, put yourself there too.

03:02:47.580 --> 03:02:50.500
Better off than being dead.

03:02:54.920 --> 03:02:57.210
You know what to do.

03:03:00.840 --> 03:03:03.680
And if you don't, I will.

03:03:07.510 --> 03:03:09.720
Get out! Take a cab.

03:03:09.890 --> 03:03:12.770
I'm busy. I got things to do. Get out.

03:03:18.320 --> 03:03:19.440
Noodles?

03:03:20.480 --> 03:03:23.400
Make up your mind fast, huh?

03:03:32.910 --> 03:03:35.620
[ Band Playing Slow Jazz Music ]

03:04:48.110 --> 03:04:50.200
What's the matter?

03:04:50.700 --> 03:04:53.200
Aren't you having a good time?

03:05:00.000 --> 03:05:02.590
Why are you going out tonight?

03:05:03.130 --> 03:05:06.380
Why bother now that prohibition
is almost over?

03:05:08.430 --> 03:05:12.350
Everybody is selling. We got
friends who have a lot of
booze they want to get rid of...

03:05:12.510 --> 03:05:16.970
...for practically nothing.
So we figure, why not?

03:05:23.150 --> 03:05:25.940
I'm going to be gone for a while.

03:05:26.240 --> 03:05:29.150
I'll be waiting at the hotel.

03:05:29.990 --> 03:05:34.120
I like it when you come home
late and wake me up.

03:05:39.710 --> 03:05:41.920
I'm not going to be home tonight.

03:05:48.920 --> 03:05:51.510
I'm not going to be home tomorrow either.

03:05:51.930 --> 03:05:55.890
I thought these things
only take a couple of hours.

03:06:00.480 --> 03:06:02.100
[ Drumroll Then Music Stops ]

03:06:02.270 --> 03:06:08.190
Ladies and gents, I drink to the demise
of Fat Moe's speakeasy.

03:06:08.490 --> 03:06:10.950
Who the hell wants to drink
here legally anyway?

03:06:11.110 --> 03:06:13.110
(Crowd Laughs)

03:06:13.280 --> 03:06:16.780
Okay. Come on, Moe, set them up.
Go on, get in there.

03:06:20.120 --> 03:06:22.120
[ Band Playing Up-Tempo Jazz Music ]

03:06:30.170 --> 03:06:31.630
- [Woman #1] Here's another one.
- [Woman #2] Ha-ha-ha.

03:06:31.800 --> 03:06:34.050
[Max]
Here's mud in your eye.

03:06:40.730 --> 03:06:42.230
Boys...

03:06:45.610 --> 03:06:47.730
Let's drink to our last shipment...

03:06:47.900 --> 03:06:50.740
Because there's more on-board
tonight than just booze.

03:06:50.900 --> 03:06:56.320
It's 10 years of our lives. Ten years
that were really worth living.

03:06:56.490 --> 03:06:57.870
Yeah.

03:07:06.040 --> 03:07:07.420
Aah.

03:07:16.350 --> 03:07:18.180
[Max]
Noodles.

03:07:19.560 --> 03:07:21.140
Noodles.

03:07:22.850 --> 03:07:25.440
-L'Chaim.
-L'Chaim.

03:07:28.440 --> 03:07:31.030
How long will I have to wait?

03:07:34.700 --> 03:07:38.200
A year and a half, more or less.

03:07:39.580 --> 03:07:41.740
Six months off for good behavior.

03:07:42.200 --> 03:07:45.040
- What are you going to do?
- Don't ask.

03:07:58.180 --> 03:08:00.180
(Sighing)

03:09:08.170 --> 03:09:10.170
(Dial Tone)

03:09:19.800 --> 03:09:21.640
[Operator]
Operator.

03:09:22.970 --> 03:09:24.140
Police, please.

03:09:24.510 --> 03:09:27.180
(Rings)

03:09:30.150 --> 03:09:32.400
Fifth Precinct. Sergeant Halloran.

03:09:35.150 --> 03:09:36.690
Hello...

03:09:37.650 --> 03:09:40.740
Who's speaking? Can I help you?

03:09:40.910 --> 03:09:42.910
- Hello?
- Yeah.

03:09:45.490 --> 03:09:47.240
I got a good tip for you.

03:10:04.300 --> 03:10:06.260
(Handle Rattles)

03:10:13.730 --> 03:10:17.530
- [Noodles] Yeah, who is it?
- [Max] Yeah, it's Max. Open the door.

03:10:23.410 --> 03:10:27.450
- What's the matter with you? You sick?
- No, I'm fine.

03:10:27.620 --> 03:10:29.290
You don't look it.

03:10:31.420 --> 03:10:34.250
Maybe you'd better
stay home tonight, huh?

03:10:34.750 --> 03:10:37.670
- Why?
- Heh.

03:10:40.130 --> 03:10:43.050
You know, I've been
watching you all night.

03:10:44.550 --> 03:10:47.390
And you've been drinking like a fish.

03:10:48.270 --> 03:10:50.680
Trying to get your courage up?

03:10:54.190 --> 03:10:57.480
We're only bringing in
a shipment of booze.

03:10:59.030 --> 03:11:02.240
It's got so you're even
scared to do that.

03:11:03.990 --> 03:11:06.740
Maybe you just better
stay home tonight.

03:11:07.780 --> 03:11:09.330
With Eve. Heh-heh-heh.

03:11:19.670 --> 03:11:24.090
Hey, Maxie, everywhere you go,
I go too. Remember that.

03:11:33.940 --> 03:11:36.400
Maybe Sharkey was right.

03:11:36.560 --> 03:11:39.360
Maybe I ought to just dump you.

03:11:48.490 --> 03:11:50.080
You're really crazy.

03:11:50.240 --> 03:11:52.160
Never say that!

03:11:52.620 --> 03:11:55.790
Don't say it!

03:12:02.590 --> 03:12:06.760
[Carol] Max made fools of us, Noodles.
He wanted to die.

03:12:06.930 --> 03:12:09.970
Did you know his old man
died in the nut house?

03:12:10.140 --> 03:12:12.970
Max didn't want to end up the same way.

03:12:13.180 --> 03:12:17.310
So he put the idea
in our heads to tip off the cops.

03:12:17.480 --> 03:12:22.360
And when they stopped the truck,
Max started shooting first...

03:12:22.530 --> 03:12:25.820
...just to get himself killed.

03:12:43.000 --> 03:12:45.340
Carol, what is this?

03:12:48.390 --> 03:12:49.550
Opening night.

03:12:51.220 --> 03:12:53.930
Fifteen years ago.

03:12:54.100 --> 03:12:56.350
Uh, who's this?

03:12:58.060 --> 03:13:01.060
Patron saint of the place.

03:13:02.440 --> 03:13:04.690
And some actress.

03:13:05.490 --> 03:13:06.860
Do you know her?

03:13:08.860 --> 03:13:10.410
No.

03:14:03.540 --> 03:14:05.840
Hello, Deborah.

03:14:13.430 --> 03:14:16.100
Aren't you going to say anything?

03:14:22.850 --> 03:14:26.190
What is someone
supposed to say after...

03:14:26.820 --> 03:14:29.860
...more than 30 years.

03:14:34.990 --> 03:14:40.950
Well, how about, "How you doing?
You're looking good."

03:14:42.960 --> 03:14:46.130
Or, "I was hoping I'd never
see you again."

03:14:48.550 --> 03:14:51.550
I never thought I would.

03:14:52.630 --> 03:14:54.970
There's a difference.

03:14:55.140 --> 03:14:58.810
Yeah. At least you recognized me,
that's something.

03:14:58.970 --> 03:15:01.980
Actresses have good memories.

03:15:11.740 --> 03:15:14.070
You want a drink?

03:15:18.280 --> 03:15:20.700
I'm having one.

03:15:31.130 --> 03:15:32.170
Margo?

03:15:33.930 --> 03:15:36.640
- Yes, miss?
- [Deborah] That's all for now.
You can go.

03:15:36.800 --> 03:15:39.010
All right, miss.

03:15:43.890 --> 03:15:46.770
She called you "miss."

03:15:47.110 --> 03:15:49.520
You never got married?

03:15:50.360 --> 03:15:51.980
No.

03:15:55.570 --> 03:15:57.110
You live alone?

03:16:05.250 --> 03:16:06.750
No.

03:16:13.590 --> 03:16:15.920
Where were you?

03:16:18.850 --> 03:16:21.260
I was out of town.

03:16:24.100 --> 03:16:26.890
Have you been back long?

03:16:27.850 --> 03:16:30.270
A couple of days.

03:16:30.440 --> 03:16:32.690
Are you staying?

03:16:44.330 --> 03:16:45.750
That depends.

03:16:48.670 --> 03:16:50.750
Why do you want to see me?

03:16:52.590 --> 03:16:54.920
Two reasons.

03:16:55.090 --> 03:16:58.340
First, I wanted to see
if you did the right thing...

03:16:58.510 --> 03:17:00.590
...turning me down to become an actress.

03:17:04.770 --> 03:17:06.350
Well?

03:17:09.150 --> 03:17:11.400
You did. You're terrific.

03:17:27.160 --> 03:17:30.250
"Age cannot wither her."

03:17:30.460 --> 03:17:33.460
It's like the play was written for you.

03:17:36.920 --> 03:17:39.380
What was the other reason?

03:17:39.590 --> 03:17:41.890
The other reason...

03:17:45.100 --> 03:17:49.430
...is to decide whether I should go
to a party tomorrow night.

03:17:56.150 --> 03:17:57.690
A party?

03:18:00.990 --> 03:18:03.490
Yeah, on Long Island.

03:18:04.990 --> 03:18:08.160
A Secretary Bailey.

03:18:12.000 --> 03:18:14.170
Do you know Secretary Bailey?

03:18:16.000 --> 03:18:17.210
No.

03:18:19.510 --> 03:18:21.970
But I was invited anyway.

03:18:30.310 --> 03:18:33.350
But if you don't know each other,
why were you invited?

03:18:33.520 --> 03:18:35.060
I don't know.

03:18:36.690 --> 03:18:38.730
I thought you might know why.

03:18:39.650 --> 03:18:41.150
Me?

03:18:41.360 --> 03:18:42.990
Why me?

03:18:48.410 --> 03:18:50.330
Because you know him.

03:18:50.500 --> 03:18:51.620
(Knocking On Door)

03:18:51.790 --> 03:18:53.250
- Who is it?
- [David] It's me, Deborah, David.

03:18:53.420 --> 03:18:56.080
- No, David.
- [David] Can I come in?

03:18:56.290 --> 03:18:59.130
No, no, no. Just wait outside,
David, I'll call you.

03:18:59.340 --> 03:19:01.720
[David]
Okay, I'll be right here.

03:19:04.510 --> 03:19:08.310
- What does Secretary
Bailey want from me?
- You came here to ask me that?

03:19:08.510 --> 03:19:11.480
- Why did he send me an invitation?
- I don't know. I don't know.

03:19:11.680 --> 03:19:16.020
Why should... ? Why should I know
about your invitations?
I don't know anything. I... 

03:19:16.230 --> 03:19:20.230
- What do you want from me? Why did
you come here?
- I know nothing, nothing.

03:19:20.400 --> 03:19:23.070
Now you're a lousy actress.

03:19:25.910 --> 03:19:28.740
Who is Secretary Bailey?

03:19:37.500 --> 03:19:41.130
Jerry Bailey is a rich businessman.

03:19:46.840 --> 03:19:51.430
He came to the United States as
a starving immigrant and
made a lot of money...

03:19:51.640 --> 03:19:55.600
...in San Francisco and Los Angeles,
where he's lived for 30 years.

03:19:55.770 --> 03:19:59.770
I know all that. It's all in the papers.
What else is there?

03:20:06.280 --> 03:20:09.280
He married a very wealthy woman.

03:20:10.580 --> 03:20:12.910
They had a child.

03:20:13.290 --> 03:20:16.330
She died when the child was born.

03:20:16.920 --> 03:20:21.460
A few years ago, he went into politics.
Moved here.

03:20:21.630 --> 03:20:26.260
That's all past history. I'm not talking
about that. I'm talking about now.

03:20:26.840 --> 03:20:29.470
Right now he's in trouble.

03:20:31.140 --> 03:20:34.520
Why can't you just tell me you've
been living with him all these years...

03:20:34.680 --> 03:20:36.640
...and that you're his lover?

03:20:45.490 --> 03:20:48.490
[Deborah]
Age can wither me, Noodles.

03:20:52.200 --> 03:20:54.830
We're both getting old.

03:21:00.170 --> 03:21:03.460
All that we have left now
are our memories.

03:21:06.380 --> 03:21:12.350
If you go to that party on Saturday
night, you won't have those anymore.

03:21:13.640 --> 03:21:16.180
Tear up that invitation.

03:21:18.480 --> 03:21:21.190
There's an exit back this way.

03:21:22.110 --> 03:21:25.030
Noodles, go through it.

03:21:27.700 --> 03:21:29.570
Keep walking.

03:21:29.780 --> 03:21:32.030
Don't turn around.

03:21:33.160 --> 03:21:35.410
Please, Noodles.

03:21:35.580 --> 03:21:38.710
I'm begging you. Please.

03:21:45.170 --> 03:21:48.720
Are you afraid that I'll turn
into a pillar of salt?

03:21:52.180 --> 03:21:55.970
If you go out that door, yes.

03:22:54.200 --> 03:22:57.160
[Deborah]
This is Secretary Bailey's son.

03:22:57.370 --> 03:23:00.870
His name's David, just like yours.

03:24:16.450 --> 03:24:19.450
[Inaudible Dialogue]

03:24:50.190 --> 03:24:53.190
[ Band Playing Cole Porter -
Night And Day ]

03:24:56.360 --> 03:24:59.360
[Inaudible Dialogue]

03:25:50.080 --> 03:25:52.250
(Door Opens)

03:25:52.420 --> 03:25:54.250
[Butler]
Please go in.

03:26:08.640 --> 03:26:10.810
[Max]
What are you waiting for?

03:26:14.650 --> 03:26:17.110
I don't understand, Mr. Bailey.

03:26:43.800 --> 03:26:45.890
Sit down, Noodles.

03:26:50.140 --> 03:26:51.940
Make yourself comfortable.

03:27:10.330 --> 03:27:13.040
I'm glad you accepted my invitation.

03:27:13.210 --> 03:27:15.210
Well, I was curious.

03:27:18.170 --> 03:27:21.300
So many important people in one place.

03:27:21.510 --> 03:27:25.390
[Max] Yes. Well, the rats usually
desert a sinking ship.

03:27:25.850 --> 03:27:29.760
But in my case, they appear to be
flocking on-board.

03:27:41.400 --> 03:27:45.240
Yeah, well, I read about
your troubles in the newspapers.

03:27:46.620 --> 03:27:51.290
But a man in your position, with all
your power and all your privileges...

03:27:51.500 --> 03:27:55.750
...has to assume a certain amount
of responsibility...

03:27:56.420 --> 03:27:58.880
...a certain amount of risk.

03:28:06.340 --> 03:28:09.100
Why did you ask me
to come here, Mr. Bailey?

03:28:12.430 --> 03:28:16.940
That invitation doesn't mean
a goddamn thing, and you know it.

03:28:17.310 --> 03:28:20.860
All that counts is what
was in that suitcase.

03:28:22.530 --> 03:28:25.240
The money and the contract.

03:28:28.070 --> 03:28:31.280
It didn't say who the contract
was on, though.

03:28:32.620 --> 03:28:35.040
Haven't you figured that out yet?

03:28:36.750 --> 03:28:38.290
You, Mr. Bailey?

03:28:52.100 --> 03:28:55.810
I haven't had a gun in my hand
for many, many years.

03:28:57.440 --> 03:29:02.980
My eyes aren't too good,
even with my glasses. My hands shake.

03:29:05.860 --> 03:29:09.860
- And I wouldn't want to miss, Mr. Bailey.
- Cut the bullshit, Noodles.

03:29:11.410 --> 03:29:14.160
I'm already a dead man.

03:29:15.080 --> 03:29:19.500
At least give me the chance
to settle the debt that I owe to you.

03:29:20.170 --> 03:29:23.670
I'll never make it before
the investigating committee.

03:29:23.840 --> 03:29:27.800
They're scared to death
I'll implicate the whole bunch of them.

03:29:28.180 --> 03:29:30.390
They got to get rid of me.

03:29:33.060 --> 03:29:36.020
Today is as good a day as any.

03:29:38.190 --> 03:29:40.560
You do it, Noodles.

03:29:41.520 --> 03:29:44.900
You're the only person
I can accept it from.

03:29:51.780 --> 03:29:54.370
You see, I found out where you were.

03:29:54.540 --> 03:29:57.620
I brought you back here for this.

03:29:58.960 --> 03:30:02.170
To even the score between you and me.

03:30:04.550 --> 03:30:07.010
You can get out through there.

03:30:14.260 --> 03:30:18.810
It leads right down to the street.
Nobody will see you.

03:30:25.570 --> 03:30:29.940
I don't know what you're talking about,
Mr. Bailey. You don't owe me a thing.

03:30:37.910 --> 03:30:44.040
Your eyes were too full of tears to see
it wasn't me burned up on that street.

03:30:44.880 --> 03:30:46.750
It was somebody else.

03:30:48.340 --> 03:30:53.260
You were too shocked to realize
that the cops were in on it too.

03:30:53.890 --> 03:30:57.100
That was a syndicate
operation, Noodles.

03:31:07.400 --> 03:31:09.400
You're crazy.

03:31:11.860 --> 03:31:16.120
You said that to me once before,
a long time ago.

03:31:16.410 --> 03:31:19.870
But my mind was never as clear
as it was at that moment.

03:31:20.620 --> 03:31:24.120
I took away your whole life from you.

03:31:24.330 --> 03:31:27.170
I've been living in your place.

03:31:28.380 --> 03:31:31.010
I took everything.

03:31:32.420 --> 03:31:34.590
I took your money.

03:31:35.220 --> 03:31:37.430
I took your girl.

03:31:38.140 --> 03:31:42.930
All I left for you was 35 years of grief
over having killed me.

03:31:44.520 --> 03:31:45.560
Now, why don't you shoot?

03:32:32.480 --> 03:32:34.490
[Inaudible Dialogue]

03:33:21.200 --> 03:33:24.120
It's true,
I have killed people, Mr. Bailey.

03:33:24.330 --> 03:33:29.080
Sometimes to defend myself,
sometimes for money.

03:33:29.370 --> 03:33:31.920
And many people used to come to us.

03:33:32.130 --> 03:33:35.050
Business partners, rivals...

03:33:35.420 --> 03:33:37.590
...lovers.

03:33:37.970 --> 03:33:42.090
Some of the jobs we took
and some we didn't.

03:33:55.480 --> 03:33:58.440
Yours is one we would never touch,
Mr. Bailey.

03:33:59.320 --> 03:34:02.280
Is this your way of getting revenge?

03:34:06.250 --> 03:34:07.830
No.

03:34:11.170 --> 03:34:14.290
It's just the way I see things.

03:35:16.980 --> 03:35:19.780
It's 10:25...

03:35:21.070 --> 03:35:24.240
...and I've got nothing left to lose.

03:35:26.370 --> 03:35:30.330
When you've been betrayed by a friend,
you hit back.

03:35:35.380 --> 03:35:37.210
Do it.

03:35:59.360 --> 03:36:01.980
You see, Mr. Secretary...

03:36:03.990 --> 03:36:06.070
...I have a story also.

03:36:07.030 --> 03:36:09.580
